  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activity 06: GLR Anglophone EWER Training</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of adopting to the current programming challenges raised by COVID-19, the Africa Programs Office (APO) has developed an alternative plan to conduct the Anglophone Regional Training on Early Warning and Early Response for Identity-Based Violence in the Great Lakes Region, while ensuring that the same quality and effectiveness as envisioned during project development prevails. The training will be conducted over 4 weeks and its components will reflect a combination of Theory, Research and Practice to expose participants to the broader knowledge, while facilitating its application in  local contexts. 

Participating Countries:
The training will involve 4 countries of Kenya, Zambia, Tanzania and Uganda of the International Conference of the Great Lakes Region (ICGLR).</narrative>
  </description>
